## A) Product Walkthrough Consolidation

### First-time visitor
- Can access auth routes and public post/profile/share routes.
- Social actions are blocked via auth prompts (like/comment/save/follow).
- Public sharing UX exists and is usable.

### Signed-up normal user
- Signup/login/forgot/reset/update flows are implemented and working.
- Onboarding nudges exist on home feed (profile photo, follow users, first post).
- Social core loop is functional: create post -> engage -> follow -> notifications.

### Active social user
- Home feed uses followed users plus fallback public mix.
- Explore and People search flows are implemented.
- Post details with likes/saves/comments/replies and share available.
- Saved and liked-content surfaces are present.

### Admin candidate
- Admin dashboard is present and functional for core ops.
- Admin can manage admins/users/posts with meaningful controls.
- But role model is still binary/hardcoded and not enterprise-safe.

